  FCX: [
    { label: "material-moving-machine-operators", share: 30.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K (fiscal year ended December 31, 2024): approximately 28,500 total employees across North America (12,900), Indonesia/Grasberg (6,400), and South America (6,700); haul truck drivers and electric shovel operators are the dominant occupation at FCX's open-pit copper mines; Morenci (Arizona, the largest US copper mine) operates continuous 24/7 shifts with hundreds of 240-ton haul trucks (CAT 797, Komatsu 930E) that move ore and waste rock; Cerro Verde (Peru) and El Abra (Chile) similarly have large open-pit haulage fleets; haul truck drivers require specialized training for ultra-class mining trucks operating on pit ramps; shovel operators run electric rope shovels and hydraulic excavators loading haul trucks at the active mine face; this occupation dominates the blue-collar workforce at large open-pit copper mines." },
    { label: "industrial-machinery-mechanics-and-maintenance-workers-and-millwrights", share: 15.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: maintenance workers at FCX's concentrator plants and mobile equipment shops are a large occupational category; plant maintenance millwrights perform preventive and corrective maintenance on ball mills (the largest pieces of rotating equipment in concentrators, grinding ore to fine particle sizes), flotation cells, thickeners, conveyor systems, and crushers; mobile equipment mechanics service and repair haul trucks, shovels, and auxiliary mining equipment (graders, bulldozers, water trucks); electrical maintenance technicians maintain drive systems, motor controls, and instrumentation at processing plants; FCX's Grasberg underground mine in Indonesia adds specialized underground mining maintenance roles." },
    { label: "construction-equipment-operators", share: 13.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: open-pit mine equipment operators beyond haul trucks include blast-hole drill operators (drilling the vertical holes into which explosives are loaded for blasting ore and waste), bulldozer operators (push-dozing material and maintaining pit floors), front-end loader operators (loading smaller material), water truck operators (dust suppression on haul roads), and grader operators (maintaining haul road surfaces); at Grasberg, underground block cave mining requires specialized LHD (load-haul-dump) operators and underground drilling equipment operators; these operators are distinct from haul truck drivers but equally essential to mine production operations." },
    { label: "top-executives", share: 12.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: management hierarchy includes mine superintendents, general foremen, and shift supervisors overseeing operations at each mine, plus district/regional management, and corporate headquarters staff in Phoenix, AZ under CEO Kathleen Quirk and CFO Maree Robertson; corporate functions include finance and accounting, legal and compliance, marketing (copper/molybdenum sales), procurement, investor relations, human resources, community and government relations (particularly critical for Grasberg operations requiring ongoing cooperation with Indonesian government), and sustainability/ESG reporting; for a 28,500-person mining company with complex international operations, management and corporate support represents ~12% of workforce." },
    { label: "mining-and-geological-engineers", share: 10.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: mine engineers are essential professionals at FCX's large mining operations; mining engineers design pit expansion phases (pushbacks), conduct geotechnical stability analysis for pit slopes, design blast patterns (blast-hole patterns, delay timing, explosive loading), perform mine planning and scheduling, and manage ore grade control; Grasberg underground block cave engineering requires specialized expertise in cave propagation, draw control, and underground infrastructure design; civil/geotechnical engineers assess stability of tailings storage facilities (a critical safety function) and waste rock dumps; survey engineers maintain the spatial accuracy of mine coordinates." },
    { label: "geoscientists", share: 8.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: geologists perform grade control sampling at active mine faces to direct ore/waste sorting decisions (grade control geology is done continuously throughout mine operations); geologists also conduct resource and reserve estimation (updating FCX's mineral reserves report annually), exploration geology (evaluating satellite deposits and new targets), and structural geology (understanding ore body geometry for mine planning); Grasberg's complex gold-rich porphyry copper ore body requires particularly specialized geology expertise; geostatistical modeling and 3D ore body models are maintained by the geological team." },
    { label: "chemical-technicians", share: 8.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: metallurgical process operators and technicians who operate copper concentrators (where ore is ground and processed via flotation to produce copper concentrate) and SX-EW (solvent extraction-electrowinning) facilities for cathode copper production; process operators monitor and adjust flotation reagent addition rates, pH levels, particle sizes, and recovery rates to optimize copper concentrate grade and recovery; laboratory technicians perform daily assays of ore feed, concentrates, tailings, and reagents; metallurgists provide technical optimization of the flotation circuits; at Morenci's large SX-EW operation, chemical process operators manage acid leach circuits, solvent extraction organics, and electrowinning tankhouses." },
    { label: "occupational-health-and-safety-specialists-and-technicians", share: 4.0, conf: "broad", note: "Freeport-McMoRan FY2024 10-K: health, safety, and environment (HSE) professionals manage mining safety programs across FCX's global operations; safety specialists conduct job hazard analyses, incident investigations, safety audits, and compliance monitoring for MSHA (Mine Safety and Health Administration) regulations at US mines and equivalent regulations internationally; industrial hygienists monitor worker exposure to silica dust, diesel particulate matter, and chemical hazards at concentrator facilities; environmental compliance staff manage tailings facility monitoring, water quality, air emissions reporting, and land reclamation planning; FCX's safety function is substantial given the inherent risks of large-scale open-pit and underground mining operations." },
  ],
