RESEARCHED.JNJ = [
  { label: "wholesale-and-manufacturing-sales-representatives", share: 22.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K (fiscal year ended December 29, 2024): approximately 138,100 total employees worldwide; after the Kenvue consumer health spin-off, JNJ operates through two segments — Innovative Medicine (pharmaceutical) and MedTech; sales representatives are among the largest categories at both segments; Innovative Medicine deploys specialty pharmaceutical sales representatives detailing oncology drugs (Darzalex/daratumumab, Erleada/apalutamide), immunology biologics (Stelara/ustekinumab, Tremfya/guselkumab, Rybrevant), pulmonary hypertension treatments, and neuroscience products to oncologists, rheumatologists, gastroenterologists, and other specialists; MedTech has a large field sales force selling orthopedic implants (DePuy Synthes), surgical platforms (Ethicon, Ottava robot), vision products (ACUVUE contact lenses, ophthalmic equipment), and cardiovascular/EP devices to hospital purchasing committees, surgeons, and ophthalmologists; field clinical specialists provide technical support during surgical procedures." },
  { label: "medical-scientists", share: 18.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: JNJ invested approximately $15.1 billion in R&D in 2024, reflecting a massive research workforce; Innovative Medicine scientists conduct target identification and validation, lead optimization in drug discovery, clinical pharmacology, translational research, clinical trial operations (CTA, CRA, data management), regulatory science (writing NDAs, BLAs, global submissions), pharmacovigilance and drug safety monitoring, and medical affairs (physician education, medical information); MedTech scientists conduct clinical research (IDE studies, post-market clinical follow-up), regulatory affairs for 510(k) and PMA submissions, and health economics/outcomes research; phase III trials like those for nipocalimab and milvexian require hundreds of clinical scientists and coordinators." },
  { label: "assemblers-and-fabricators", share: 15.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: JNJ operates pharmaceutical manufacturing facilities (API synthesis, bioreactor fermentation for biologics, fill-finish for injectables, solid dose tablet manufacturing) and MedTech manufacturing facilities (orthopedic implant machining and finishing, suture manufacturing, surgical instrument assembly, contact lens manufacturing, medical device electromechanical assembly); pharmaceutical manufacturing requires technicians who operate fermenters, bioreactors, fill-finish lines, lyophilizers, and packaging equipment; MedTech production workers assemble complex surgical instruments, ophthalmic devices, and interventional cardiology devices; FDA's cGMP regulations require rigorous documentation and process control at all manufacturing facilities, increasing the staffing requirements per unit of output." },
  { label: "top-executives", share: 12.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: JNJ's management structure includes a large corporate leadership team (CEO, CFO, CHRO, CMO, Chief R&D Officer), sector presidents for each segment (Innovative Medicine, MedTech), regional presidents for North America, EMEA, Asia-Pacific, and Latin America, country managers, franchise/therapeutic area vice presidents, business unit presidents for major product lines (DePuy Synthes, Ethicon, Vision), and operations directors for manufacturing sites; the global scale and complexity of two large diversified healthcare segments requires a substantial management layer; MedTech's 100+ acquisitions also add integration management overhead." },
  { label: "biomedical-engineers", share: 10.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: biomedical engineering is central to JNJ's MedTech segment; engineers design next-generation orthopedic implants (hip, knee, spine systems with novel fixation and bearing technologies), develop robotic surgery platforms (Ottava robotic surgical system in development, Monarch endoscopy robot), design interventional cardiology and electrophysiology devices, create ophthalmic devices, and develop advanced wound closure technologies; MedTech product development requires mechanical, biomedical, materials, and electrical engineers working in cross-functional teams; manufacturing engineers support process development and scale-up for complex medical devices; with 15 major MedTech products launched in 2024, the engineering pipeline is active." },
  { label: "computer-programmers", share: 8.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: technology is embedded across JNJ's operations; software engineers build and maintain clinical trial management systems (CTMS), electronic data capture (EDC) systems, regulatory submission platforms (eCTD), pharmacovigilance case processing systems, drug interaction databases, and JNJ's commercial digital marketing platforms; MedTech's robotics and digital surgery initiatives require significant embedded software engineering (Ottava robot, Monarch endoscopy AI, digital pathology platforms); JNJ's enterprise technology organization supports ERP (SAP), CRM (Veeva for pharma), manufacturing execution systems (MES), and supply chain platforms across global operations; data science teams support clinical trial analytics and real-world evidence studies." },
  { label: "quality-control-inspectors", share: 8.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: quality is a core function at JNJ given FDA, EMA, and other global regulatory oversight of pharmaceutical and medical device manufacturing; quality assurance and control staff include batch record reviewers who examine manufacturing documentation for each drug batch before product release, QC analysts who perform testing (sterility, potency, purity, particulate testing for injectables), incoming materials inspectors, finished product inspectors at MedTech manufacturing sites, calibration technicians for manufacturing equipment, deviation investigators who document and CAPA (corrective and preventive action) investigate manufacturing nonconformances, and validation specialists who execute IQ/OQ/PQ qualification protocols for manufacturing equipment and cleaning validation studies." },
  { label: "biochemists-and-biophysicists", share: 7.0, conf: "broad", note: "Johnson & Johnson FY2024 10-K: drug discovery and early research at Janssen (JNJ's pharmaceutical R&D organization) employs biochemists for target biology characterization, enzyme kinetics, binding assays, cell-based functional assays, and early ADME screening; structural biologists use X-ray crystallography, cryo-EM, and NMR to elucidate protein-ligand interactions for drug design; biophysicists characterize biologic (antibody) candidates for stability, aggregation, and biophysical properties; process biochemists develop biomanufacturing processes for antibody-drug conjugates (ADCs), bispecific antibodies, and CAR-T therapies; protein engineering scientists design novel biologic scaffolds; JNJ's oncology pipeline (CAR-T, bispecific antibodies) is particularly dependent on advanced biochemistry and cell biology expertise." },
];

